110 /// runOnMachineFunction - This uses the emitInstruction() ----
111 /// method to print assembly for each instruction. ----
112 /// ----
113 bool ARMAsmPrinter::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &MF) { 0
114 AFI = MF.getInfo(); 0
115 MCP = MF.getConstantPool(); 0
116 Subtarget = &MF.getSubtarget(); 0
117 ----
118 SetupMachineFunction(MF); 0
119 const Function &F = MF.getFunction(); 0
120 const TargetMachine& TM = MF.getTarget(); 0
121 ----
122 // Collect all globals that had their storage promoted to a constant pool. ----
123 // Functions are emitted before variables, so this accumulates promoted ----
124 // globals from all functions in PromotedGlobals. ----
125 for (const auto *GV : AFI->getGlobalsPromotedToConstantPool()) 0
126 PromotedGlobals.insert(GV); 0
127 ----
128 // Calculate this function's optimization goal. ----
129 unsigned OptimizationGoal; ----
130 if (F.hasOptNone()) 0
131 // For best debugging illusion, speed and small size sacrificed ----
132 OptimizationGoal = 6; 0
133 else if (F.hasMinSize()) 0
134 // Aggressively for small size, speed and debug illusion sacrificed ----
135 OptimizationGoal = 4; 0
136 else if (F.hasOptSize()) 0
137 // For small size, but speed and debugging illusion preserved ----
138 OptimizationGoal = 3; 0
139 else if (TM.getOptLevel() == CodeGenOpt::Aggressive) 0
140 // Aggressively for speed, small size and debug illusion sacrificed ----
141 OptimizationGoal = 2; 0
142 else if (TM.getOptLevel() > CodeGenOpt::None) 0
143 // For speed, but small size and good debug illusion preserved ----
144 OptimizationGoal = 1; 0
145 else // TM.getOptLevel() == CodeGenOpt::None ----
146 // For good debugging, but speed and small size preserved ----
147 OptimizationGoal = 5; 0
148 ----
149 // Combine a new optimization goal with existing ones. ----
150 if (OptimizationGoals == -1) // uninitialized goals 0
151 OptimizationGoals = OptimizationGoal; 0
152 else if (OptimizationGoals != (int)OptimizationGoal) // conflicting goals 0
153 OptimizationGoals = 0; 0
154 ----
155 if (Subtarget->isTargetCOFF()) { 0
156 bool Internal = F.hasInternalLinkage(); 0
157 COFF::SymbolStorageClass Scl = Internal ? COFF::IMAGE_SYM_CLASS_STATIC 0
158 : COFF::IMAGE_SYM_CLASS_EXTERNAL; ----
159 int Type = COFF::IMAGE_SYM_DTYPE_FUNCTION << COFF::SCT_COMPLEX_TYPE_SHIFT; 0
160 ----
161 OutStreamer->beginCOFFSymbolDef(CurrentFnSym); 0
162 OutStreamer->emitCOFFSymbolStorageClass(Scl); 0
163 OutStreamer->emitCOFFSymbolType(Type); 0
164 OutStreamer->endCOFFSymbolDef(); 0
165 } ----
166 ----
167 // Emit the rest of the function body. ----
168 emitFunctionBody(); 0
169 ----
170 // Emit the XRay table for this function. ----
171 emitXRayTable(); 0
172 ----
173 // If we need V4T thumb mode Register Indirect Jump pads, emit them. ----
174 // These are created per function, rather than per TU, since it's ----
175 // relatively easy to exceed the thumb branch range within a TU. ----
176 if (! ThumbIndirectPads.empty()) { 0
177 OutStreamer->emitAssemblerFlag(MCAF_Code16); 0
178 emitAlignment(Align(2)); 0
179 for (std::pair &TIP : ThumbIndirectPads) { 0
180 OutStreamer->emitLabel(TIP.second); 0
181 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(ARM::tBX) 0
182 .addReg(TIP.first) 0
183 // Add predicate operands. ----
184 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0
185 .addReg(0)); 0
186 } ----
187 ThumbIndirectPads.clear(); 0
188 } ----
189 ----
190 // We didn't modify anything. ----
191 return false; 0
192 } ----

194 void ARMAsmPrinter::PrintSymbolOperand(const MachineOperand &MO, 0
195 raw_ostream &O) { ----
196 assert(MO.isGlobal() && "caller should check MO.isGlobal"); 0
197 unsigned TF = MO.getTargetFlags(); 0
198 if (TF & ARMII::MO_LO16) 0
199 O << ":lower16:"; 0
200 else if (TF & ARMII::MO_HI16) 0
201 O << ":upper16:"; 0
202 else if (TF & ARMII::MO_LO_0_7) 0
203 O << ":lower0_7:"; 0
204 else if (TF & ARMII::MO_LO_8_15) 0
205 O << ":lower8_15:"; 0
206 else if (TF & ARMII::MO_HI_0_7) 0
207 O << ":upper0_7:"; 0
208 else if (TF & ARMII::MO_HI_8_15) 0
209 O << ":upper8_15:"; 0
210 ----
211 GetARMGVSymbol(MO.getGlobal(), TF)->print(O, MAI); 0
212 printOffset(MO.getOffset(), O); 0
213 } 0

215 void ARMAsmPrinter::printOperand(const MachineInstr *MI, int OpNum, 0
216 raw_ostream &O) { ----
217 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(OpNum); 0
218 ----
219 switch (MO.getType()) { 0
220 default: llvm_unreachable(""); 0
221 case MachineOperand::MO_Register: { 0
222 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
223 assert(Reg.isPhysical()); 0
224 assert(!MO.getSubReg() && "Subregs should be eliminated!"); 0
225 if(ARM::GPRPairRegClass.contains(Reg)) { 0
226 const MachineFunction &MF = *MI->getParent()->getParent(); 0
227 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = MF.getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
228 Reg = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::gsub_0); 0
229 } ----
230 O << ARMInstPrinter::getRegisterName(Reg); 0
231 break; 0
232 } ----
233 case MachineOperand::MO_Immediate: { 0
234 O << '#'; 0
235 unsigned TF = MO.getTargetFlags(); 0
236 if (TF == ARMII::MO_LO16) 0
237 O << ":lower16:"; 0
238 else if (TF == ARMII::MO_HI16) 0
239 O << ":upper16:"; 0
240 else if (TF == ARMII::MO_LO_0_7) 0
241 O << ":lower0_7:"; 0
242 else if (TF == ARMII::MO_LO_8_15) 0
243 O << ":lower8_15:"; 0
244 else if (TF == ARMII::MO_HI_0_7) 0
245 O << ":upper0_7:"; 0
246 else if (TF == ARMII::MO_HI_8_15) 0
247 O << ":upper8_15:"; 0
248 O << MO.getImm(); 0
249 break; 0
250 } ----
251 case MachineOperand::MO_MachineBasicBlock: 0
252 MO.getMBB()->getSymbol()->print(O, MAI); 0
253 return; 0
254 case MachineOperand::MO_GlobalAddress: { 0
255 PrintSymbolOperand(MO, O); 0
256 break; 0
257 } ----
258 case MachineOperand::MO_ConstantPoolIndex: 0
259 if (Subtarget->genExecuteOnly()) 0
260 llvm_unreachable("execute-only should not generate constant pools"); 0
261 GetCPISymbol(MO.getIndex())->print(O, MAI); 0
262 break; 0
263 } ----
264 } ----

286 bool ARMAsmPrinter::PrintAsmOperand(const MachineInstr *MI, unsigned OpNum, 0
287 const char *ExtraCode, raw_ostream &O) { ----
288 // Does this asm operand have a single letter operand modifier? ----
289 if (ExtraCode && ExtraCode[0]) { 0
290 if (ExtraCode[1] != 0) return true; // Unknown modifier. 0
291 ----
292 switch (ExtraCode[0]) { 0
293 default: 0
294 // See if this is a generic print operand ----
295 return AsmPrinter::PrintAsmOperand(MI, OpNum, ExtraCode, O); 0
296 case 'P': // Print a VFP double precision register. 0
297 case 'q': // Print a NEON quad precision register. ----
298 printOperand(MI, OpNum, O); 0
299 return false; 0
300 case 'y': // Print a VFP single precision register as indexed double. 0
301 if (MI->getOperand(OpNum).isReg()) { 0
302 MCRegister Reg = MI->getOperand(OpNum).getReg().asMCReg(); 0
303 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
304 // Find the 'd' register that has this 's' register as a sub-register, ----
305 // and determine the lane number. ----
306 for (MCPhysReg SR : TRI->superregs(Reg)) { 0
307 if (!ARM::DPRRegClass.contains(SR)) 0
308 continue; 0
309 bool Lane0 = TRI->getSubReg(SR, ARM::ssub_0) == Reg; 0
310 O << ARMInstPrinter::getRegisterName(SR) << (Lane0 ? "[0]" : "[1]"); 0
311 return false; 0
312 } ----
313 } ----
314 return true; 0
315 case 'B': // Bitwise inverse of integer or symbol without a preceding #. 0
316 if (!MI->getOperand(OpNum).isImm()) 0
317 return true; 0
318 O << ~(MI->getOperand(OpNum).getImm()); 0
319 return false; 0
320 case 'L': // The low 16 bits of an immediate constant. 0
321 if (!MI->getOperand(OpNum).isImm()) 0
322 return true; 0
323 O << (MI->getOperand(OpNum).getImm() & 0xffff); 0
324 return false; 0
325 case 'M': { // A register range suitable for LDM/STM. 0
326 if (!MI->getOperand(OpNum).isReg()) 0
327 return true; 0
328 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(OpNum); 0
329 Register RegBegin = MO.getReg(); 0
330 // This takes advantage of the 2 operand-ness of ldm/stm and that we've ----
331 // already got the operands in registers that are operands to the ----
332 // inline asm statement. ----
333 O << "{"; 0
334 if (ARM::GPRPairRegClass.contains(RegBegin)) { 0
335 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
336 Register Reg0 = TRI->getSubReg(RegBegin, ARM::gsub_0); 0
337 O << ARMInstPrinter::getRegisterName(Reg0) << ", "; 0
338 RegBegin = TRI->getSubReg(RegBegin, ARM::gsub_1); 0
339 } ----
340 O << ARMInstPrinter::getRegisterName(RegBegin); 0
341 ----
342 // FIXME: The register allocator not only may not have given us the ----
343 // registers in sequence, but may not be in ascending registers. This ----
344 // will require changes in the register allocator that'll need to be ----
345 // propagated down here if the operands change. ----
346 unsigned RegOps = OpNum + 1; 0
347 while (MI->getOperand(RegOps).isReg()) { 0
348 O << ", " 0
349 << ARMInstPrinter::getRegisterName(MI->getOperand(RegOps).getReg()); 0
350 RegOps++; 0
351 } ----
352 ----
353 O << "}"; 0
354 ----
355 return false; 0
356 } ----
357 case 'R': // The most significant register of a pair. 0
358 case 'Q': { // The least significant register of a pair. ----
359 if (OpNum == 0) 0
360 return true; 0
361 const MachineOperand &FlagsOP = MI->getOperand(OpNum - 1); 0
362 if (!FlagsOP.isImm()) 0
363 return true; 0
364 unsigned Flags = FlagsOP.getImm(); 0
365 ----
366 // This operand may not be the one that actually provides the register. If ----
367 // it's tied to a previous one then we should refer instead to that one ----
368 // for registers and their classes. ----
369 unsigned TiedIdx; ----
370 if (InlineAsm::isUseOperandTiedToDef(Flags, TiedIdx)) { 0
371 for (OpNum = InlineAsm::MIOp_FirstOperand; TiedIdx; --TiedIdx) { 0
372 unsigned OpFlags = MI->getOperand(OpNum).getImm(); 0
373 OpNum += InlineAsm::getNumOperandRegisters(OpFlags) + 1; 0
374 } ----
375 Flags = MI->getOperand(OpNum).getImm(); 0
376 ----
377 // Later code expects OpNum to be pointing at the register rather than ----
378 // the flags. ----
379 OpNum += 1; 0
380 } ----
381 ----
382 unsigned NumVals = InlineAsm::getNumOperandRegisters(Flags); 0
383 unsigned RC; ----
384 bool FirstHalf; ----
385 const ARMBaseTargetMachine &ATM = 0
386 static_cast(TM); ----
387 ----
388 // 'Q' should correspond to the low order register and 'R' to the high ----
389 // order register. Whether this corresponds to the upper or lower half ----
390 // depends on the endianess mode. ----
391 if (ExtraCode[0] == 'Q') 0
392 FirstHalf = ATM.isLittleEndian(); 0
393 else ----
394 // ExtraCode[0] == 'R'. ----
395 FirstHalf = !ATM.isLittleEndian(); 0
396 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
397 if (InlineAsm::hasRegClassConstraint(Flags, RC) && 0
398 ARM::GPRPairRegClass.hasSubClassEq(TRI->getRegClass(RC))) { 0
399 if (NumVals != 1) 0
400 return true; 0
401 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(OpNum); 0
402 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
403 return true; 0
404 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
405 Register Reg = ----
406 TRI->getSubReg(MO.getReg(), FirstHalf ? ARM::gsub_0 : ARM::gsub_1); 0
407 O << ARMInstPrinter::getRegisterName(Reg); 0
408 return false; 0
409 } ----
410 if (NumVals != 2) 0
411 return true; 0
412 unsigned RegOp = FirstHalf ? OpNum : OpNum + 1; 0
413 if (RegOp >= MI->getNumOperands()) 0
414 return true; 0
415 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(RegOp); 0
416 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
417 return true; 0
418 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
419 O << ARMInstPrinter::getRegisterName(Reg); 0
420 return false; 0
421 } ----
422 ----
423 case 'e': // The low doubleword register of a NEON quad register. 0
424 case 'f': { // The high doubleword register of a NEON quad register. ----
425 if (!MI->getOperand(OpNum).isReg()) 0
426 return true; 0
427 Register Reg = MI->getOperand(OpNum).getReg(); 0
428 if (!ARM::QPRRegClass.contains(Reg)) 0
429 return true; 0
430 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
431 Register SubReg = ----
432 TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ExtraCode[0] == 'e' ? ARM::dsub_0 : ARM::dsub_1); 0
433 O << ARMInstPrinter::getRegisterName(SubReg); 0
434 return false; 0
435 } ----
436 ----
437 // This modifier is not yet supported. ----
438 case 'h': // A range of VFP/NEON registers suitable for VLD1/VST1. 0
439 return true; 0
440 case 'H': { // The highest-numbered register of a pair. 0
441 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(OpNum); 0
442 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
443 return true; 0
444 const MachineFunction &MF = *MI->getParent()->getParent(); 0
445 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = MF.getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
446 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
447 if(!ARM::GPRPairRegClass.contains(Reg)) 0
448 return false; 0
449 Reg = TRI->getSubReg(Reg, ARM::gsub_1); 0
450 O << ARMInstPrinter::getRegisterName(Reg); 0
451 return false; 0
452 } ----
453 } ----
454 } ----
455 ----
456 printOperand(MI, OpNum, O); 0
457 return false; 0
458 } ----

460 bool ARMAsmPrinter::PrintAsmMemoryOperand(const MachineInstr *MI, 0
461 unsigned OpNum, const char *ExtraCode, ----
462 raw_ostream &O) { ----
463 // Does this asm operand have a single letter operand modifier? ----
464 if (ExtraCode && ExtraCode[0]) { 0
465 if (ExtraCode[1] != 0) return true; // Unknown modifier. 0
466 ----
467 switch (ExtraCode[0]) { 0
468 case 'A': // A memory operand for a VLD1/VST1 instruction. 0
469 default: return true; // Unknown modifier. 0
470 case 'm': // The base register of a memory operand. 0
471 if (!MI->getOperand(OpNum).isReg()) 0
472 return true; 0
473 O << ARMInstPrinter::getRegisterName(MI->getOperand(OpNum).getReg()); 0
474 return false; 0
475 } ----
476 } ----
477 ----
478 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(OpNum); 0
479 assert(MO.isReg() && "unexpected inline asm memory operand"); 0
480 O << "[" << ARMInstPrinter::getRegisterName(MO.getReg()) << "]"; 0
481 return false; 0
482 } ----

484 static bool isThumb(const MCSubtargetInfo& STI) { 0
485 return STI.hasFeature(ARM::ModeThumb); 0
486 } ----
487 ----
488 void ARMAsmPrinter::emitInlineAsmEnd(const MCSubtargetInfo &StartInfo, 0
489 const MCSubtargetInfo *EndInfo) const { ----
490 // If either end mode is unknown (EndInfo == NULL) or different than ----
491 // the start mode, then restore the start mode. ----
492 const bool WasThumb = isThumb(StartInfo); 0
493 if (!EndInfo || WasThumb != isThumb(*EndInfo)) { 0
494 OutStreamer->emitAssemblerFlag(WasThumb ? MCAF_Code16 : MCAF_Code32); 0
495 } ----
496 } 0
497 ----
498 void ARMAsmPrinter::emitStartOfAsmFile(Module &M) { 0
499 const Triple &TT = TM.getTargetTriple(); 0
500 // Use unified assembler syntax. ----
501 OutStreamer->emitAssemblerFlag(MCAF_SyntaxUnified); 0
502 ----
503 // Emit ARM Build Attributes ----
504 if (TT.isOSBinFormatELF()) 0
505 emitAttributes(); 0
506 ----
507 // Use the triple's architecture and subarchitecture to determine ----
508 // if we're thumb for the purposes of the top level code16 assembler ----
509 // flag. ----
510 if (!M.getModuleInlineAsm().empty() && TT.isThumb()) 0
511 OutStreamer->emitAssemblerFlag(MCAF_Code16); 0
512 } 0
513 ----
514 static void ----
515 emitNonLazySymbolPointer(MCStreamer &OutStreamer, MCSymbol *StubLabel, 0
516 MachineModuleInfoImpl::StubValueTy &MCSym) { ----
517 // L_foo$stub: ----
518 OutStreamer.emitLabel(StubLabel); 0
519 // .indirect_symbol _foo ----
520 OutStreamer.emitSymbolAttribute(MCSym.getPointer(), MCSA_IndirectSymbol); 0
521 ----
522 if (MCSym.getInt()) 0
523 // External to current translation unit. ----
524 OutStreamer.emitIntValue(0, 4/*size*/); 0
525 else ----
526 // Internal to current translation unit. ----
527 // ----
528 // When we place the LSDA into the TEXT section, the type info ----
529 // pointers need to be indirect and pc-rel. We accomplish this by ----
530 // using NLPs; however, sometimes the types are local to the file. ----
531 // We need to fill in the value for the NLP in those cases. ----
532 OutStreamer.emitValue( 0
533 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MCSym.getPointer(), OutStreamer.getContext()), 0
534 4 /*size*/); ----
535 } 0
536 ----
537 ----
538 void ARMAsmPrinter::emitEndOfAsmFile(Module &M) { 0
539 const Triple &TT = TM.getTargetTriple(); 0
540 if (TT.isOSBinFormatMachO()) { 0
541 // All darwin targets use mach-o. ----
542 const TargetLoweringObjectFileMachO &TLOFMacho = ----
543 static_cast(getObjFileLowering()); 0
544 MachineModuleInfoMachO &MMIMacho = ----
545 MMI->getObjFileInfo(); 0
546 ----
547 // Output non-lazy-pointers for external and common global variables. ----
548 MachineModuleInfoMachO::SymbolListTy Stubs = MMIMacho.GetGVStubList(); 0
549 ----
550 if (!Stubs.empty()) { 0
551 // Switch with ".non_lazy_symbol_pointer" directive. ----
552 OutStreamer->switchSection(TLOFMacho.getNonLazySymbolPointerSection()); 0
553 emitAlignment(Align(4)); 0
554 ----
555 for (auto &Stub : Stubs) 0
556 emitNonLazySymbolPointer(*OutStreamer, Stub.first, Stub.second); 0
557 ----
558 Stubs.clear(); 0
559 OutStreamer->addBlankLine(); 0
560 } ----
561 ----
562 Stubs = MMIMacho.GetThreadLocalGVStubList(); 0
563 if (!Stubs.empty()) { 0
564 // Switch with ".non_lazy_symbol_pointer" directive. ----
565 OutStreamer->switchSection(TLOFMacho.getThreadLocalPointerSection()); 0
566 emitAlignment(Align(4)); 0
567 ----
568 for (auto &Stub : Stubs) 0
569 emitNonLazySymbolPointer(*OutStreamer, Stub.first, Stub.second); 0
570 ----
571 Stubs.clear(); 0
572 OutStreamer->addBlankLine(); 0
573 } ----
574 ----
575 // Funny Darwin hack: This flag tells the linker that no global symbols ----
576 // contain code that falls through to other global symbols (e.g. the obvious ----
577 // implementation of multiple entry points). If this doesn't occur, the ----
578 // linker can safely perform dead code stripping. Since LLVM never ----
579 // generates code that does this, it is always safe to set. ----
580 OutStreamer->emitAssemblerFlag(MCAF_SubsectionsViaSymbols); 0
581 } 0
582 ----
583 // The last attribute to be emitted is ABI_optimization_goals ----
584 MCTargetStreamer &TS = *OutStreamer->getTargetStreamer(); 0
585 ARMTargetStreamer &ATS = static_cast(TS); 0
586 ----
587 if (OptimizationGoals > 0 && 0
588 (Subtarget->isTargetAEABI() || Subtarget->isTargetGNUAEABI() || 0
589 Subtarget->isTargetMuslAEABI())) 0
590 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_optimization_goals, OptimizationGoals); 0
591 OptimizationGoals = -1; 0
592 ----
593 ATS.finishAttributeSection(); 0
594 } 0
595 ----
596 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
597 // Helper routines for emitStartOfAsmFile() and emitEndOfAsmFile() ----
598 // FIXME: ----
599 // The following seem like one-off assembler flags, but they actually need ----
600 // to appear in the .ARM.attributes section in ELF. ----
601 // Instead of subclassing the MCELFStreamer, we do the work here. ----
602 ----
603 // Returns true if all functions have the same function attribute value. ----
604 // It also returns true when the module has no functions. ----
605 static bool checkFunctionsAttributeConsistency(const Module &M, StringRef Attr, 0
606 StringRef Value) { ----
607 return !any_of(M, [&](const Function &F) { 0
608 return F.getFnAttribute(Attr).getValueAsString() != Value; 0
609 }); 0
610 } ----
611 // Returns true if all functions have the same denormal mode. ----
612 // It also returns true when the module has no functions. ----
613 static bool checkDenormalAttributeConsistency(const Module &M, 0
614 StringRef Attr, ----
615 DenormalMode Value) { ----
616 return !any_of(M, [&](const Function &F) { 0
617 StringRef AttrVal = F.getFnAttribute(Attr).getValueAsString(); 0
618 return parseDenormalFPAttribute(AttrVal) != Value; 0
619 }); 0
620 } ----
621 ----
622 void ARMAsmPrinter::emitAttributes() { 0
623 MCTargetStreamer &TS = *OutStreamer->getTargetStreamer(); 0
624 ARMTargetStreamer &ATS = static_cast(TS); 0
625 ----
626 ATS.emitTextAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::conformance, "2.09"); 0
627 ----
628 ATS.switchVendor("aeabi"); 0
629 ----
630 // Compute ARM ELF Attributes based on the default subtarget that ----
631 // we'd have constructed. The existing ARM behavior isn't LTO clean ----
632 // anyhow. ----
633 // FIXME: For ifunc related functions we could iterate over and look ----
634 // for a feature string that doesn't match the default one. ----
635 const Triple &TT = TM.getTargetTriple(); 0
636 StringRef CPU = TM.getTargetCPU(); 0
637 StringRef FS = TM.getTargetFeatureString(); 0
638 std::string ArchFS = ARM_MC::ParseARMTriple(TT, CPU); 0
639 if (!FS.empty()) { 0
640 if (!ArchFS.empty()) 0
641 ArchFS = (Twine(ArchFS) + "," + FS).str(); 0
642 else ----
643 ArchFS = std::string(FS); 0
644 } ----
645 const ARMBaseTargetMachine &ATM = 0
646 static_cast(TM); ----
647 const ARMSubtarget STI(TT, std::string(CPU), ArchFS, ATM, 0
648 ATM.isLittleEndian()); 0
649 ----
650 // Emit build attributes for the available hardware. ----
651 ATS.emitTargetAttributes(STI); 0
652 ----
653 // RW data addressing. ----
654 if (isPositionIndependent()) { 0
655 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_PCS_RW_data, 0
656 ARMBuildAttrs::AddressRWPCRel); ----
657 } else if (STI.isRWPI()) { 0
658 // RWPI specific attributes. ----
659 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_PCS_RW_data, 0
660 ARMBuildAttrs::AddressRWSBRel); ----
661 } ----
662 ----
663 // RO data addressing. ----
664 if (isPositionIndependent() || STI.isROPI()) { 0
665 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_PCS_RO_data, 0
666 ARMBuildAttrs::AddressROPCRel); ----
667 } ----
668 ----
669 // GOT use. ----
670 if (isPositionIndependent()) { 0
671 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_PCS_GOT_use, 0
672 ARMBuildAttrs::AddressGOT); ----
673 } else { ----
674 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_PCS_GOT_use, 0
675 ARMBuildAttrs::AddressDirect); ----
676 } ----
677 ----
678 // Set FP Denormals. ----
679 if (checkDenormalAttributeConsistency(*MMI->getModule(), "denormal-fp-math", 0
680 DenormalMode::getPreserveSign())) ----
681 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_FP_denormal, 0
682 ARMBuildAttrs::PreserveFPSign); ----
683 else if (checkDenormalAttributeConsistency(*MMI->getModule(), 0
684 "denormal-fp-math", ----
685 DenormalMode::getPositiveZero())) ----
686 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_FP_denormal, 0
687 ARMBuildAttrs::PositiveZero); ----
688 else if (!TM.Options.UnsafeFPMath) 0
689 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_FP_denormal, 0
690 ARMBuildAttrs::IEEEDenormals); ----
691 else { ----
692 if (!STI.hasVFP2Base()) { 0
693 // When the target doesn't have an FPU (by design or ----
694 // intention), the assumptions made on the software support ----
695 // mirror that of the equivalent hardware support *if it ----
696 // existed*. For v7 and better we indicate that denormals are ----
697 // flushed preserving sign, and for V6 we indicate that ----
698 // denormals are flushed to positive zero. ----
699 if (STI.hasV7Ops()) 0
700 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_FP_denormal, 0
701 ARMBuildAttrs::PreserveFPSign); ----
702 } else if (STI.hasVFP3Base()) { 0
703 // In VFPv4, VFPv4U, VFPv3, or VFPv3U, it is preserved. That is, ----
704 // the sign bit of the zero matches the sign bit of the input or ----
705 // result that is being flushed to zero. ----
706 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_FP_denormal, 0
707 ARMBuildAttrs::PreserveFPSign); ----
708 } ----
709 // For VFPv2 implementations it is implementation defined as ----
710 // to whether denormals are flushed to positive zero or to ----
711 // whatever the sign of zero is (ARM v7AR ARM 2.7.5). Historically ----
712 // LLVM has chosen to flush this to positive zero (most likely for ----
713 // GCC compatibility), so that's the chosen value here (the ----
714 // absence of its emission implies zero). ----
715 } ----
716 ----
717 // Set FP exceptions and rounding ----
718 if (checkFunctionsAttributeConsistency(*MMI->getModule(), 0
719 "no-trapping-math", "true") || 0
720 TM.Options.NoTrappingFPMath) 0
721 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_FP_exceptions, 0
722 ARMBuildAttrs::Not_Allowed); ----
723 else if (!TM.Options.UnsafeFPMath) { 0
724 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_FP_exceptions, ARMBuildAttrs::Allowed); 0
725 ----
726 // If the user has permitted this code to choose the IEEE 754 ----
727 // rounding at run-time, emit the rounding attribute. ----
728 if (TM.Options.HonorSignDependentRoundingFPMathOption) 0
729 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_FP_rounding, ARMBuildAttrs::Allowed); 0
730 } ----
731 ----
732 // TM.Options.NoInfsFPMath && TM.Options.NoNaNsFPMath is the ----
733 // equivalent of GCC's -ffinite-math-only flag. ----
734 if (TM.Options.NoInfsFPMath && TM.Options.NoNaNsFPMath) 0
735 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_FP_number_model, 0
736 ARMBuildAttrs::Allowed); ----
737 else ----
738 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_FP_number_model, 0
739 ARMBuildAttrs::AllowIEEE754); ----
740 ----
741 // FIXME: add more flags to ARMBuildAttributes.h ----
742 // 8-bytes alignment stuff. ----
743 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_align_needed, 1); 0
744 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_align_preserved, 1); 0
745 ----
746 // Hard float. Use both S and D registers and conform to AAPCS-VFP. ----
747 if (STI.isAAPCS_ABI() && TM.Options.FloatABIType == FloatABI::Hard) 0
748 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_VFP_args, ARMBuildAttrs::HardFPAAPCS); 0
749 ----
750 // FIXME: To support emitting this build attribute as GCC does, the ----
751 // -mfp16-format option and associated plumbing must be ----
752 // supported. For now the __fp16 type is exposed by default, so this ----
753 // attribute should be emitted with value 1. ----
754 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_FP_16bit_format, 0
755 ARMBuildAttrs::FP16FormatIEEE); ----
756 ----
757 if (const Module *SourceModule = MMI->getModule()) { 0
758 // ABI_PCS_wchar_t to indicate wchar_t width ----
759 // FIXME: There is no way to emit value 0 (wchar_t prohibited). ----
760 if (auto WCharWidthValue = mdconst::extract_or_null( 0
761 SourceModule->getModuleFlag("wchar_size"))) { 0
762 int WCharWidth = WCharWidthValue->getZExtValue(); 0
763 assert((WCharWidth == 2 || WCharWidth == 4) && 0
764 "wchar_t width must be 2 or 4 bytes"); ----
765 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_PCS_wchar_t, WCharWidth); 0
766 } ----
767 ----
768 // ABI_enum_size to indicate enum width ----
769 // FIXME: There is no way to emit value 0 (enums prohibited) or value 3 ----
770 // (all enums contain a value needing 32 bits to encode). ----
771 if (auto EnumWidthValue = mdconst::extract_or_null( 0
772 SourceModule->getModuleFlag("min_enum_size"))) { 0
773 int EnumWidth = EnumWidthValue->getZExtValue(); 0
774 assert((EnumWidth == 1 || EnumWidth == 4) && 0
775 "Minimum enum width must be 1 or 4 bytes"); ----
776 int EnumBuildAttr = EnumWidth == 1 ? 1 : 2; 0
777 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_enum_size, EnumBuildAttr); 0
778 } ----
779 ----
780 auto *PACValue = mdconst::extract_or_null( 0
781 SourceModule->getModuleFlag("sign-return-address")); 0
782 if (PACValue && PACValue->isOne()) { 0
783 // If "+pacbti" is used as an architecture extension, ----
784 // Tag_PAC_extension is emitted in ----
785 // ARMTargetStreamer::emitTargetAttributes(). ----
786 if (!STI.hasPACBTI()) { 0
787 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::PAC_extension, 0
788 ARMBuildAttrs::AllowPACInNOPSpace); ----
789 } ----
790 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::PACRET_use, ARMBuildAttrs::PACRETUsed); 0
791 } ----
792 ----
793 auto *BTIValue = mdconst::extract_or_null( 0
794 SourceModule->getModuleFlag("branch-target-enforcement")); 0
795 if (BTIValue && BTIValue->isOne()) { 0
796 // If "+pacbti" is used as an architecture extension, ----
797 // Tag_BTI_extension is emitted in ----
798 // ARMTargetStreamer::emitTargetAttributes(). ----
799 if (!STI.hasPACBTI()) { 0
800 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::BTI_extension, 0
801 ARMBuildAttrs::AllowBTIInNOPSpace); ----
802 } ----
803 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::BTI_use, ARMBuildAttrs::BTIUsed); 0
804 } ----
805 } ----
806 ----
807 // We currently do not support using R9 as the TLS pointer. ----
808 if (STI.isRWPI()) 0
809 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_PCS_R9_use, 0
810 ARMBuildAttrs::R9IsSB); ----
811 else if (STI.isR9Reserved()) 0
812 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_PCS_R9_use, 0
813 ARMBuildAttrs::R9Reserved); ----
814 else ----
815 ATS.emitAttribute(ARMBuildAttrs::ABI_PCS_R9_use, 0
816 ARMBuildAttrs::R9IsGPR); ----
817 } 0
818 ----
819 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
820 ----
821 static MCSymbol *getBFLabel(StringRef Prefix, unsigned FunctionNumber, 0
822 unsigned LabelId, MCContext &Ctx) { ----
823 ----
824 MCSymbol *Label = Ctx.getOrCreateSymbol(Twine(Prefix) 0
825 + "BF" + Twine(FunctionNumber) + "_" + Twine(LabelId)); 0
826 return Label; 0
827 } ----
828 ----
829 static MCSymbol *getPICLabel(StringRef Prefix, unsigned FunctionNumber, 0
830 unsigned LabelId, MCContext &Ctx) { ----
831 ----
832 MCSymbol *Label = Ctx.getOrCreateSymbol(Twine(Prefix) 0
833 + "PC" + Twine(FunctionNumber) + "_" + Twine(LabelId)); 0
834 return Label; 0
835 } ----
836 ----
837 static MCSymbolRefExpr::VariantKind ----
838 getModifierVariantKind(ARMCP::ARMCPModifier Modifier) { 0
839 switch (Modifier) { 0
840 case ARMCP::no_modifier: 0
841 return MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None; 0
842 case ARMCP::TLSGD: 0
843 return MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_TLSGD; 0
844 case ARMCP::TPOFF: 0
845 return MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_TPOFF; 0
846 case ARMCP::GOTTPOFF: 0
847 return MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_GOTTPOFF; 0
848 case ARMCP::SBREL: 0
849 return MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_ARM_SBREL; 0
850 case ARMCP::GOT_PREL: 0
851 return MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_ARM_GOT_PREL; 0
852 case ARMCP::SECREL: 0
853 return MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_SECREL; 0
854 } ----
855 llvm_unreachable("Invalid ARMCPModifier!"); 0
856 } ----
857 ----
858 MCSymbol *ARMAsmPrinter::GetARMGVSymbol(const GlobalValue *GV, 0
859 unsigned char TargetFlags) { ----
860 if (Subtarget->isTargetMachO()) { 0
861 bool IsIndirect = ----
862 (TargetFlags & ARMII::MO_NONLAZY) && Subtarget->isGVIndirectSymbol(GV); 0
863 ----
864 if (!IsIndirect) 0
865 return getSymbol(GV); 0
866 ----
867 // FIXME: Remove this when Darwin transition to @GOT like syntax. ----
868 MCSymbol *MCSym = getSymbolWithGlobalValueBase(GV, "$non_lazy_ptr"); 0
869 MachineModuleInfoMachO &MMIMachO = ----
870 MMI->getObjFileInfo(); 0
871 MachineModuleInfoImpl::StubValueTy &StubSym = ----
872 GV->isThreadLocal() ? MMIMachO.getThreadLocalGVStubEntry(MCSym) 0
873 : MMIMachO.getGVStubEntry(MCSym); 0
874 ----
875 if (!StubSym.getPointer()) 0
876 StubSym = MachineModuleInfoImpl::StubValueTy(getSymbol(GV), 0
877 !GV->hasInternalLinkage()); 0
878 return MCSym; 0
879 } else if (Subtarget->isTargetCOFF()) { 0
880 assert(Subtarget->isTargetWindows() && 0
881 "Windows is the only supported COFF target"); ----
882 ----
883 bool IsIndirect = 0
884 (TargetFlags & (ARMII::MO_DLLIMPORT | ARMII::MO_COFFSTUB)); 0
885 if (!IsIndirect) 0
886 return getSymbol(GV); 0
887 ----
888 SmallString<128> Name; 0
889 if (TargetFlags & ARMII::MO_DLLIMPORT) 0
890 Name = "__imp_"; 0
891 else if (TargetFlags & ARMII::MO_COFFSTUB) 0
892 Name = ".refptr."; 0
893 getNameWithPrefix(Name, GV); 0
894 ----
895 MCSymbol *MCSym = OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol(Name); 0
896 ----
897 if (TargetFlags & ARMII::MO_COFFSTUB) { 0
898 MachineModuleInfoCOFF &MMICOFF = ----
899 MMI->getObjFileInfo(); 0
900 MachineModuleInfoImpl::StubValueTy &StubSym = ----
901 MMICOFF.getGVStubEntry(MCSym); 0
902 ----
903 if (!StubSym.getPointer()) 0
904 StubSym = MachineModuleInfoImpl::StubValueTy(getSymbol(GV), true); 0
905 } ----
906 ----
907 return MCSym; 0
908 } else if (Subtarget->isTargetELF()) { 0
909 return getSymbolPreferLocal(*GV); 0
910 } ----
911 llvm_unreachable("unexpected target"); 0
912 } ----
913 ----
914 void ARMAsmPrinter::emitMachineConstantPoolValue( 0
915 MachineConstantPoolValue *MCPV) { ----
916 const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout(); 0
917 int Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(MCPV->getType()); 0
918 ----
919 ARMConstantPoolValue *ACPV = static_cast(MCPV); 0
920 ----
921 if (ACPV->isPromotedGlobal()) { 0
922 // This constant pool entry is actually a global whose storage has been ----
923 // promoted into the constant pool. This global may be referenced still ----
924 // by debug information, and due to the way AsmPrinter is set up, the debug ----
925 // info is immutable by the time we decide to promote globals to constant ----
926 // pools. Because of this, we need to ensure we emit a symbol for the global ----
927 // with private linkage (the default) so debug info can refer to it. ----
928 // ----
929 // However, if this global is promoted into several functions we must ensure ----
930 // we don't try and emit duplicate symbols! ----
931 auto *ACPC = cast(ACPV); 0
932 for (const auto *GV : ACPC->promotedGlobals()) { 0
933 if (!EmittedPromotedGlobalLabels.count(GV)) { 0
934 MCSymbol *GVSym = getSymbol(GV); 0
935 OutStreamer->emitLabel(GVSym); 0
936 EmittedPromotedGlobalLabels.insert(GV); 0
937 } ----
938 } ----
939 return emitGlobalConstant(DL, ACPC->getPromotedGlobalInit()); 0
940 } ----
941 ----
942 MCSymbol *MCSym; ----
943 if (ACPV->isLSDA()) { 0
944 MCSym = getMBBExceptionSym(MF->front()); 0
945 } else if (ACPV->isBlockAddress()) { 0
946 const BlockAddress *BA = ----
947 cast(ACPV)->getBlockAddress(); 0
948 MCSym = GetBlockAddressSymbol(BA); 0
949 } else if (ACPV->isGlobalValue()) { 0
950 const GlobalValue *GV = cast(ACPV)->getGV(); 0
951 ----
952 // On Darwin, const-pool entries may get the "FOO$non_lazy_ptr" mangling, so ----
953 // flag the global as MO_NONLAZY. ----
954 unsigned char TF = Subtarget->isTargetMachO() ? ARMII::MO_NONLAZY : 0; 0
955 MCSym = GetARMGVSymbol(GV, TF); 0
956 } else if (ACPV->isMachineBasicBlock()) { 0
957 const MachineBasicBlock *MBB = cast(ACPV)->getMBB(); 0
958 MCSym = MBB->getSymbol(); 0
959 } else { ----
960 assert(ACPV->isExtSymbol() && "unrecognized constant pool value"); 0
961 auto Sym = cast(ACPV)->getSymbol(); 0
962 MCSym = GetExternalSymbolSymbol(Sym); 0
963 } ----
964 ----
965 // Create an MCSymbol for the reference. ----
966 const MCExpr *Expr = ----
967 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MCSym, getModifierVariantKind(ACPV->getModifier()), 0
968 OutContext); ----
969 ----
970 if (ACPV->getPCAdjustment()) { 0
971 MCSymbol *PCLabel = ----
972 getPICLabel(DL.getPrivateGlobalPrefix(), getFunctionNumber(), 0
973 ACPV->getLabelId(), OutContext); ----
974 const MCExpr *PCRelExpr = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(PCLabel, OutContext); 0
975 PCRelExpr = ----
976 MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(PCRelExpr, 0
977 MCConstantExpr::create(ACPV->getPCAdjustment(), 0
978 OutContext), ----
979 OutContext); ----
980 if (ACPV->mustAddCurrentAddress()) { 0
981 // We want "( - .)", but MC doesn't have a concept of the '.' ----
982 // label, so just emit a local label end reference that instead. ----
983 MCSymbol *DotSym = OutContext.createTempSymbol(); 0
984 OutStreamer->emitLabel(DotSym); 0
985 const MCExpr *DotExpr = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(DotSym, OutContext); 0
986 PCRelExpr = MCBinaryExpr::createSub(PCRelExpr, DotExpr, OutContext); 0
987 } ----
988 Expr = MCBinaryExpr::createSub(Expr, PCRelExpr, OutContext); 0
989 } ----
990 OutStreamer->emitValue(Expr, Size); 0
991 } ----
992 ----
993 void ARMAsmPrinter::emitJumpTableAddrs(const MachineInstr *MI) { 0
994 const MachineOperand &MO1 = MI->getOperand(1); 0
995 unsigned JTI = MO1.getIndex(); 0
996 ----
997 // Make sure the Thumb jump table is 4-byte aligned. This will be a nop for ----
998 // ARM mode tables. ----
999 emitAlignment(Align(4)); 0
1000 ----
1001 // Emit a label for the jump table. ----
1002 MCSymbol *JTISymbol = GetARMJTIPICJumpTableLabel(JTI); 0
1003 OutStreamer->emitLabel(JTISymbol); 0
1004 ----
1005 // Mark the jump table as data-in-code. ----
1006 OutStreamer->emitDataRegion(MCDR_DataRegionJT32); 0
1007 ----
1008 // Emit each entry of the table. ----
1009 const MachineJumpTableInfo *MJTI = MF->getJumpTableInfo(); 0
1010 const std::vector &JT = MJTI->getJumpTables(); 0
1011 const std::vector &JTBBs = JT[JTI].MBBs; 0
1012 ----
1013 for (MachineBasicBlock *MBB : JTBBs) { 0
1014 // Construct an MCExpr for the entry. We want a value of the form: ----
1015 // (BasicBlockAddr - TableBeginAddr) ----
1016 // ----
1017 // For example, a table with entries jumping to basic blocks BB0 and BB1 ----
1018 // would look like: ----
1019 // LJTI_0_0: ----
1020 // .word (LBB0 - LJTI_0_0) ----
1021 // .word (LBB1 - LJTI_0_0) ----
1022 const MCExpr *Expr = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MBB->getSymbol(), OutContext); 0
1023 ----
1024 if (isPositionIndependent() || Subtarget->isROPI()) 0
1025 Expr = MCBinaryExpr::createSub(Expr, MCSymbolRefExpr::create(JTISymbol, 0
1026 OutContext), ----
1027 OutContext); ----
1028 // If we're generating a table of Thumb addresses in static relocation ----
1029 // model, we need to add one to keep interworking correctly. ----
1030 else if (AFI->isThumbFunction()) 0
1031 Expr = MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(Expr, MCConstantExpr::create(1,OutContext), 0
1032 OutContext); ----
1033 OutStreamer->emitValue(Expr, 4); 0
1034 } ----
1035 // Mark the end of jump table data-in-code region. ----
1036 OutStreamer->emitDataRegion(MCDR_DataRegionEnd); 0
1037 } 0
1038 ----
1039 void ARMAsmPrinter::emitJumpTableInsts(const MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1040 const MachineOperand &MO1 = MI->getOperand(1); 0
1041 unsigned JTI = MO1.getIndex(); 0
1042 ----
1043 // Make sure the Thumb jump table is 4-byte aligned. This will be a nop for ----
1044 // ARM mode tables. ----
1045 emitAlignment(Align(4)); 0
1046 ----
1047 // Emit a label for the jump table. ----
1048 MCSymbol *JTISymbol = GetARMJTIPICJumpTableLabel(JTI); 0
1049 OutStreamer->emitLabel(JTISymbol); 0
1050 ----
1051 // Emit each entry of the table. ----
1052 const MachineJumpTableInfo *MJTI = MF->getJumpTableInfo(); 0
1053 const std::vector &JT = MJTI->getJumpTables(); 0
1054 const std::vector &JTBBs = JT[JTI].MBBs; 0
1055 ----
1056 for (MachineBasicBlock *MBB : JTBBs) { 0
1057 const MCExpr *MBBSymbolExpr = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MBB->getSymbol(), 0
1058 OutContext); ----
1059 // If this isn't a TBB or TBH, the entries are direct branch instructions. ----
1060 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(ARM::t2B) 0
1061 .addExpr(MBBSymbolExpr) 0
1062 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0
1063 .addReg(0)); 0
1064 } ----
1065 } 0
1066 ----
1067 void ARMAsmPrinter::emitJumpTableTBInst(const MachineInstr *MI, 0
1068 unsigned OffsetWidth) { ----
1069 assert((OffsetWidth == 1 || OffsetWidth == 2) && "invalid tbb/tbh width"); 0
1070 const MachineOperand &MO1 = MI->getOperand(1); 0
1071 unsigned JTI = MO1.getIndex(); 0
1072 ----
1073 if (Subtarget->isThumb1Only()) 0
1074 emitAlignment(Align(4)); 0
1075 ----
1076 MCSymbol *JTISymbol = GetARMJTIPICJumpTableLabel(JTI); 0
1077 OutStreamer->emitLabel(JTISymbol); 0
1078 ----
1079 // Emit each entry of the table. ----
1080 const MachineJumpTableInfo *MJTI = MF->getJumpTableInfo(); 0
1081 const std::vector &JT = MJTI->getJumpTables(); 0
1082 const std::vector &JTBBs = JT[JTI].MBBs; 0
1083 ----
1084 // Mark the jump table as data-in-code. ----
1085 OutStreamer->emitDataRegion(OffsetWidth == 1 ? MCDR_DataRegionJT8 0
1086 : MCDR_DataRegionJT16); ----
1087 ----
1088 for (auto *MBB : JTBBs) { 0
1089 const MCExpr *MBBSymbolExpr = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MBB->getSymbol(), 0
1090 OutContext); ----
1091 // Otherwise it's an offset from the dispatch instruction. Construct an ----
1092 // MCExpr for the entry. We want a value of the form: ----
1093 // (BasicBlockAddr - TBBInstAddr + 4) / 2 ----
1094 // ----
1095 // For example, a TBB table with entries jumping to basic blocks BB0 and BB1 ----
1096 // would look like: ----
1097 // LJTI_0_0: ----
1098 // .byte (LBB0 - (LCPI0_0 + 4)) / 2 ----
1099 // .byte (LBB1 - (LCPI0_0 + 4)) / 2 ----
1100 // where LCPI0_0 is a label defined just before the TBB instruction using ----
1101 // this table. ----
1102 MCSymbol *TBInstPC = GetCPISymbol(MI->getOperand(0).getImm()); 0
1103 const MCExpr *Expr = MCBinaryExpr::createAdd( 0
1104 MCSymbolRefExpr::create(TBInstPC, OutContext), 0
1105 MCConstantExpr::create(4, OutContext), OutContext); 0
1106 Expr = MCBinaryExpr::createSub(MBBSymbolExpr, Expr, OutContext); 0
1107 Expr = MCBinaryExpr::createDiv(Expr, MCConstantExpr::create(2, OutContext), 0
1108 OutContext); ----
1109 OutStreamer->emitValue(Expr, OffsetWidth); 0
1110 } ----
1111 // Mark the end of jump table data-in-code region. 32-bit offsets use ----
1112 // actual branch instructions here, so we don't mark those as a data-region ----
1113 // at all. ----
1114 OutStreamer->emitDataRegion(MCDR_DataRegionEnd); 0
1115 ----
1116 // Make sure the next instruction is 2-byte aligned. ----
1117 emitAlignment(Align(2)); 0
1118 } 0
1119 ----
1120 void ARMAsmPrinter::EmitUnwindingInstruction(const MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1121 assert(MI->getFlag(MachineInstr::FrameSetup) && 0
1122 "Only instruction which are involved into frame setup code are allowed"); ----
1123 ----
1124 MCTargetStreamer &TS = *OutStreamer->getTargetStreamer(); 0
1125 ARMTargetStreamer &ATS = static_cast(TS); 0
1126 const MachineFunction &MF = *MI->getParent()->getParent(); 0
1127 const TargetRegisterInfo *TargetRegInfo = ----
1128 MF.getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
1129 const MachineRegisterInfo &MachineRegInfo = MF.getRegInfo(); 0
1130 ----
1131 Register FramePtr = TargetRegInfo->getFrameRegister(MF); 0
1132 unsigned Opc = MI->getOpcode(); 0
1133 unsigned SrcReg, DstReg; ----
1134 ----
1135 switch (Opc) { 0
1136 case ARM::tPUSH: 0
1137 // special case: tPUSH does not have src/dst regs. ----
1138 SrcReg = DstReg = ARM::SP; 0
1139 break; 0
1140 case ARM::tLDRpci: 0
1141 case ARM::t2MOVi16: ----
1142 case ARM::t2MOVTi16: ----
1143 case ARM::tMOVi8: ----
1144 case ARM::tADDi8: ----
1145 case ARM::tLSLri: ----
1146 // special cases: ----
1147 // 1) for Thumb1 code we sometimes materialize the constant via constpool ----
1148 // load. ----
1149 // 2) for Thumb1 execute only code we materialize the constant via the ----
1150 // following pattern: ----
1151 // movs r3, #:upper8_15: ----
1152 // lsls r3, #8 ----
1153 // adds r3, #:upper0_7: ----
1154 // lsls r3, #8 ----
1155 // adds r3, #:lower8_15: ----
1156 // lsls r3, #8 ----
1157 // adds r3, #:lower0_7: ----
1158 // So we need to special-case MOVS, ADDS and LSLS, and keep track of ----
1159 // where we are in the sequence with the simplest of state machines. ----
1160 // 3) for Thumb2 execute only code we materialize the constant via ----
1161 // immediate constants in 2 separate instructions (MOVW/MOVT). ----
1162 SrcReg = ~0U; 0
1163 DstReg = MI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1164 break; 0
1165 default: 0
1166 SrcReg = MI->getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1167 DstReg = MI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1168 break; 0
1169 } ----
1170 ----
1171 // Try to figure out the unwinding opcode out of src / dst regs. ----
1172 if (MI->mayStore()) { 0
1173 // Register saves. ----
1174 assert(DstReg == ARM::SP && 0
1175 "Only stack pointer as a destination reg is supported"); ----
1176 ----
1177 SmallVector RegList; 0
1178 // Skip src & dst reg, and pred ops. ----
1179 unsigned StartOp = 2 + 2; 0
1180 // Use all the operands. ----
1181 unsigned NumOffset = 0; 0
1182 // Amount of SP adjustment folded into a push, before the ----
1183 // registers are stored (pad at higher addresses). ----
1184 unsigned PadBefore = 0; 0
1185 // Amount of SP adjustment folded into a push, after the ----
1186 // registers are stored (pad at lower addresses). ----
1187 unsigned PadAfter = 0; 0
1188 ----
1189 switch (Opc) { 0
1190 default: 0
1191 MI->print(errs()); 0
1192 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported opcode for unwinding information"); 0
1193 case ARM::tPUSH: 0
1194 // Special case here: no src & dst reg, but two extra imp ops. ----
1195 StartOp = 2; NumOffset = 2; 0
1196 [[fallthrough]]; ----
1197 case ARM::STMDB_UPD: 0
1198 case ARM::t2STMDB_UPD: ----
1199 case ARM::VSTMDDB_UPD: ----
1200 assert(SrcReg == ARM::SP && 0
1201 "Only stack pointer as a source reg is supported"); ----
1202 for (unsigned i = StartOp, NumOps = MI->getNumOperands() - NumOffset; 0
1203 i != NumOps; ++i) { 0
1204 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(i); 0
1205 // Actually, there should never be any impdef stuff here. Skip it ----
1206 // temporary to workaround PR11902. ----
1207 if (MO.isImplicit()) 0
1208 continue; 0
1209 // Registers, pushed as a part of folding an SP update into the ----
1210 // push instruction are marked as undef and should not be ----
1211 // restored when unwinding, because the function can modify the ----
1212 // corresponding stack slots. ----
1213 if (MO.isUndef()) { 0
1214 assert(RegList.empty() && 0
1215 "Pad registers must come before restored ones"); ----
1216 unsigned Width = ----
1217 TargetRegInfo->getRegSizeInBits(MO.getReg(), MachineRegInfo) / 8; 0
1218 PadAfter += Width; 0
1219 continue; 0
1220 } 0
1221 // Check for registers that are remapped (for a Thumb1 prologue that ----
1222 // saves high registers). ----
1223 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1224 if (unsigned RemappedReg = AFI->EHPrologueRemappedRegs.lookup(Reg)) 0
1225 Reg = RemappedReg; 0
1226 RegList.push_back(Reg); 0
1227 } ----
1228 break; 0
1229 case ARM::STR_PRE_IMM: 0
1230 case ARM::STR_PRE_REG: ----
1231 case ARM::t2STR_PRE: ----
1232 assert(MI->getOperand(2).getReg() == ARM::SP && 0
1233 "Only stack pointer as a source reg is supported"); ----
1234 if (unsigned RemappedReg = AFI->EHPrologueRemappedRegs.lookup(SrcReg)) 0
1235 SrcReg = RemappedReg; 0
1236 ----
1237 RegList.push_back(SrcReg); 0
1238 break; 0
1239 case ARM::t2STRD_PRE: 0
1240 assert(MI->getOperand(3).getReg() == ARM::SP && 0
1241 "Only stack pointer as a source reg is supported"); ----
1242 SrcReg = MI->getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1243 if (unsigned RemappedReg = AFI->EHPrologueRemappedRegs.lookup(SrcReg)) 0
1244 SrcReg = RemappedReg; 0
1245 RegList.push_back(SrcReg); 0
1246 SrcReg = MI->getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
1247 if (unsigned RemappedReg = AFI->EHPrologueRemappedRegs.lookup(SrcReg)) 0
1248 SrcReg = RemappedReg; 0
1249 RegList.push_back(SrcReg); 0
1250 PadBefore = -MI->getOperand(4).getImm() - 8; 0
1251 break; 0
1252 } ----
1253 if (MAI->getExceptionHandlingType() == ExceptionHandling::ARM) { 0
1254 if (PadBefore) 0
1255 ATS.emitPad(PadBefore); 0
1256 ATS.emitRegSave(RegList, Opc == ARM::VSTMDDB_UPD); 0
1257 // Account for the SP adjustment, folded into the push. ----
1258 if (PadAfter) 0
1259 ATS.emitPad(PadAfter); 0
1260 } ----
1261 } else { 0
1262 // Changes of stack / frame pointer. ----
1263 if (SrcReg == ARM::SP) { 0
1264 int64_t Offset = 0; 0
1265 switch (Opc) { 0
1266 default: 0
1267 MI->print(errs()); 0
1268 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported opcode for unwinding information"); 0
1269 case ARM::MOVr: 0
1270 case ARM::tMOVr: ----
1271 Offset = 0; 0
1272 break; 0
1273 case ARM::ADDri: 0
1274 case ARM::t2ADDri: ----
1275 case ARM::t2ADDri12: ----
1276 case ARM::t2ADDspImm: ----
1277 case ARM::t2ADDspImm12: ----
1278 Offset = -MI->getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1279 break; 0
1280 case ARM::SUBri: 0
1281 case ARM::t2SUBri: ----
1282 case ARM::t2SUBri12: ----
1283 case ARM::t2SUBspImm: ----
1284 case ARM::t2SUBspImm12: ----
1285 Offset = MI->getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1286 break; 0
1287 case ARM::tSUBspi: 0
1288 Offset = MI->getOperand(2).getImm()*4; 0
1289 break; 0
1290 case ARM::tADDspi: 0
1291 case ARM::tADDrSPi: ----
1292 Offset = -MI->getOperand(2).getImm()*4; 0
1293 break; 0
1294 case ARM::tADDhirr: 0
1295 Offset = 0
1296 -AFI->EHPrologueOffsetInRegs.lookup(MI->getOperand(2).getReg()); 0
1297 break; 0
1298 } ----
1299 ----
1300 if (MAI->getExceptionHandlingType() == ExceptionHandling::ARM) { 0
1301 if (DstReg == FramePtr && FramePtr != ARM::SP) 0
1302 // Set-up of the frame pointer. Positive values correspond to "add" ----
1303 // instruction. ----
1304 ATS.emitSetFP(FramePtr, ARM::SP, -Offset); 0
1305 else if (DstReg == ARM::SP) { 0
1306 // Change of SP by an offset. Positive values correspond to "sub" ----
1307 // instruction. ----
1308 ATS.emitPad(Offset); 0
1309 } else { ----
1310 // Move of SP to a register. Positive values correspond to an "add" ----
1311 // instruction. ----
1312 ATS.emitMovSP(DstReg, -Offset); 0
1313 } ----
1314 } ----
1315 } else if (DstReg == ARM::SP) { 0
1316 MI->print(errs()); 0
1317 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported opcode for unwinding information"); 0
1318 } else { ----
1319 int64_t Offset = 0; 0
1320 switch (Opc) { 0
1321 case ARM::tMOVr: 0
1322 // If a Thumb1 function spills r8-r11, we copy the values to low ----
1323 // registers before pushing them. Record the copy so we can emit the ----
1324 // correct ".save" later. ----
1325 AFI->EHPrologueRemappedRegs[DstReg] = SrcReg; 0
1326 break; 0
1327 case ARM::tLDRpci: { 0
1328 // Grab the constpool index and check, whether it corresponds to ----
1329 // original or cloned constpool entry. ----
1330 unsigned CPI = MI->getOperand(1).getIndex(); 0
1331 const MachineConstantPool *MCP = MF.getConstantPool(); 0
1332 if (CPI >= MCP->getConstants().size()) 0
1333 CPI = AFI->getOriginalCPIdx(CPI); 0
1334 assert(CPI != -1U && "Invalid constpool index"); 0
1335 ----
1336 // Derive the actual offset. ----
1337 const MachineConstantPoolEntry &CPE = MCP->getConstants()[CPI]; 0
1338 assert(!CPE.isMachineConstantPoolEntry() && "Invalid constpool entry"); 0
1339 Offset = cast(CPE.Val.ConstVal)->getSExtValue(); 0
1340 AFI->EHPrologueOffsetInRegs[DstReg] = Offset; 0
1341 break; 0
1342 } ----
1343 case ARM::t2MOVi16: 0
1344 Offset = MI->getOperand(1).getImm(); 0
1345 AFI->EHPrologueOffsetInRegs[DstReg] = Offset; 0
1346 break; 0
1347 case ARM::t2MOVTi16: 0
1348 Offset = MI->getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1349 AFI->EHPrologueOffsetInRegs[DstReg] |= (Offset << 16); 0
1350 break; 0
1351 case ARM::tMOVi8: 0
1352 Offset = MI->getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1353 AFI->EHPrologueOffsetInRegs[DstReg] = Offset; 0
1354 break; 0
1355 case ARM::tLSLri: 0
1356 assert(MI->getOperand(3).getImm() == 8 && 0
1357 "The shift amount is not equal to 8"); ----
1358 assert(MI->getOperand(2).getReg() == MI->getOperand(0).getReg() && 0
1359 "The source register is not equal to the destination register"); ----
1360 AFI->EHPrologueOffsetInRegs[DstReg] <<= 8; 0
1361 break; 0
1362 case ARM::tADDi8: 0
1363 assert(MI->getOperand(2).getReg() == MI->getOperand(0).getReg() && 0
1364 "The source register is not equal to the destination register"); ----
1365 Offset = MI->getOperand(3).getImm(); 0
1366 AFI->EHPrologueOffsetInRegs[DstReg] += Offset; 0
1367 break; 0
1368 case ARM::t2PAC: 0
1369 case ARM::t2PACBTI: ----
1370 AFI->EHPrologueRemappedRegs[ARM::R12] = ARM::RA_AUTH_CODE; 0
1371 break; 0
1372 default: 0
1373 MI->print(errs()); 0
1374 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported opcode for unwinding information"); 0
1375 } ----
1376 } ----
1377 } ----
1378 } 0
1379 ----
1380 // Simple pseudo-instructions have their lowering (with expansion to real ----
1381 // instructions) auto-generated. ----
1382 #include "ARMGenMCPseudoLowering.inc" ----
1383 ----
1384 void ARMAsmPrinter::emitInstruction(const MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1385 // TODOD FIXME: Enable feature predicate checks once all the test pass. ----
1386 // ARM_MC::verifyInstructionPredicates(MI->getOpcode(), ----
1387 // getSubtargetInfo().getFeatureBits()); ----
1388 ----
1389 const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout(); 0
1390 MCTargetStreamer &TS = *OutStreamer->getTargetStreamer(); 0
1391 ARMTargetStreamer &ATS = static_cast(TS); 0
1392 ----
1393 // If we just ended a constant pool, mark it as such. ----
1394 if (InConstantPool && MI->getOpcode() != ARM::CONSTPOOL_ENTRY) { 0
1395 OutStreamer->emitDataRegion(MCDR_DataRegionEnd); 0
1396 InConstantPool = false; 0
1397 } ----
1398 ----
1399 // Emit unwinding stuff for frame-related instructions ----
1400 if (Subtarget->isTargetEHABICompatible() && 0
1401 MI->getFlag(MachineInstr::FrameSetup)) 0
1402 EmitUnwindingInstruction(MI); 0
1403 ----
1404 // Do any auto-generated pseudo lowerings. ----
1405 if (emitPseudoExpansionLowering(*OutStreamer, MI)) 0
1406 return; 0
1407 ----
1408 assert(!convertAddSubFlagsOpcode(MI->getOpcode()) && 0
1409 "Pseudo flag setting opcode should be expanded early"); ----
1410 ----
1411 // Check for manual lowerings. ----
1412 unsigned Opc = MI->getOpcode(); 0
1413 switch (Opc) { 0
1414 case ARM::t2MOVi32imm: llvm_unreachable("Should be lowered by thumb2it pass"); 0
1415 case ARM::DBG_VALUE: llvm_unreachable("Should be handled by generic printing"); 0
1416 case ARM::LEApcrel: 0
1417 case ARM::tLEApcrel: ----
1418 case ARM::t2LEApcrel: { ----
1419 // FIXME: Need to also handle globals and externals ----
1420 MCSymbol *CPISymbol = GetCPISymbol(MI->getOperand(1).getIndex()); 0
1421 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(MI->getOpcode() == 0
1422 ARM::t2LEApcrel ? ARM::t2ADR 0
1423 : (MI->getOpcode() == ARM::tLEApcrel ? ARM::tADR 0
1424 : ARM::ADR)) ----
1425 .addReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
1426 .addExpr(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(CPISymbol, OutContext)) 0
1427 // Add predicate operands. ----
1428 .addImm(MI->getOperand(2).getImm()) 0
1429 .addReg(MI->getOperand(3).getReg())); 0
1430 return; 0
1431 } ----
1432 case ARM::LEApcrelJT: 0
1433 case ARM::tLEApcrelJT: ----
1434 case ARM::t2LEApcrelJT: { ----
1435 MCSymbol *JTIPICSymbol = ----
1436 GetARMJTIPICJumpTableLabel(MI->getOperand(1).getIndex()); 0
1437 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(MI->getOpcode() == 0
1438 ARM::t2LEApcrelJT ? ARM::t2ADR 0
1439 : (MI->getOpcode() == ARM::tLEApcrelJT ? ARM::tADR 0
1440 : ARM::ADR)) ----
1441 .addReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
1442 .addExpr(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(JTIPICSymbol, OutContext)) 0
1443 // Add predicate operands. ----
1444 .addImm(MI->getOperand(2).getImm()) 0
1445 .addReg(MI->getOperand(3).getReg())); 0
1446 return; 0
1447 } ----
1448 // Darwin call instructions are just normal call instructions with different ----
1449 // clobber semantics (they clobber R9). ----
1450 case ARM::BX_CALL: { 0
1451 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(ARM::MOVr) 0
1452 .addReg(ARM::LR) 0
1453 .addReg(ARM::PC) 0
1454 // Add predicate operands. ----
1455 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0
1456 .addReg(0) 0
1457 // Add 's' bit operand (always reg0 for this) ----
1458 .addReg(0)); 0
1459 ----
1460 assert(Subtarget->hasV4TOps()); 0
1461 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(ARM::BX) 0
1462 .addReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg())); 0
1463 return; 0
1464 } ----
1465 case ARM::tBX_CALL: { 0
1466 if (Subtarget->hasV5TOps()) 0
1467 llvm_unreachable("Expected BLX to be selected for v5t+"); 0
1468 ----
1469 // On ARM v4t, when doing a call from thumb mode, we need to ensure ----
1470 // that the saved lr has its LSB set correctly (the arch doesn't ----
1471 // have blx). ----
1472 // So here we generate a bl to a small jump pad that does bx rN. ----
1473 // The jump pads are emitted after the function body. ----
1474 ----
1475 Register TReg = MI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1476 MCSymbol *TRegSym = nullptr; 0
1477 for (std::pair &TIP : ThumbIndirectPads) { 0
1478 if (TIP.first == TReg) { 0
1479 TRegSym = TIP.second; 0
1480 break; 0
1481 } ----
1482 } ----
1483 ----
1484 if (!TRegSym) { 0
1485 TRegSym = OutContext.createTempSymbol(); 0
1486 ThumbIndirectPads.push_back(std::make_pair(TReg, TRegSym)); 0
1487 } ----
1488 ----
1489 // Create a link-saving branch to the Reg Indirect Jump Pad. ----
1490 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(ARM::tBL) 0
1491 // Predicate comes first here. ----
1492 .addImm(ARMCC::AL).addReg(0) 0
1493 .addExpr(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(TRegSym, OutContext))); 0
1494 return; 0
1495 } ----
1496 case ARM::BMOVPCRX_CALL: { 0
1497 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(ARM::MOVr) 0
1498 .addReg(ARM::LR) 0
1499 .addReg(ARM::PC) 0
1500 // Add predicate operands. ----
1501 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0
1502 .addReg(0) 0
1503 // Add 's' bit operand (always reg0 for this) ----
1504 .addReg(0)); 0
1505 ----
1506 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(ARM::MOVr) 0
1507 .addReg(ARM::PC) 0
1508 .addReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
1509 // Add predicate operands. ----
1510 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0
1511 .addReg(0) 0
1512 // Add 's' bit operand (always reg0 for this) ----
1513 .addReg(0)); 0
1514 return; 0
1515 } ----
1516 case ARM::BMOVPCB_CALL: { 0
1517 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(ARM::MOVr) 0
1518 .addReg(ARM::LR) 0
1519 .addReg(ARM::PC) 0
1520 // Add predicate operands. ----
1521 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0
1522 .addReg(0) 0
1523 // Add 's' bit operand (always reg0 for this) ----
1524 .addReg(0)); 0
1525 ----
1526 const MachineOperand &Op = MI->getOperand(0); 0
1527 const GlobalValue *GV = Op.getGlobal(); 0
1528 const unsigned TF = Op.getTargetFlags(); 0
1529 MCSymbol *GVSym = GetARMGVSymbol(GV, TF); 0
1530 const MCExpr *GVSymExpr = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(GVSym, OutContext); 0
1531 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(ARM::Bcc) 0
1532 .addExpr(GVSymExpr) 0
1533 // Add predicate operands. ----
1534 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0
1535 .addReg(0)); 0
1536 return; 0
1537 } ----
1538 case ARM::MOVi16_ga_pcrel: 0
1539 case ARM::t2MOVi16_ga_pcrel: { ----
1540 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1541 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opc == ARM::MOVi16_ga_pcrel? ARM::MOVi16 : ARM::t2MOVi16); 0
1542 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg())); 0
1543 ----
1544 unsigned TF = MI->getOperand(1).getTargetFlags(); 0
1545 const GlobalValue *GV = MI->getOperand(1).getGlobal(); 0
1546 MCSymbol *GVSym = GetARMGVSymbol(GV, TF); 0
1547 const MCExpr *GVSymExpr = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(GVSym, OutContext); 0
1548 ----
1549 MCSymbol *LabelSym = ----
1550 getPICLabel(DL.getPrivateGlobalPrefix(), getFunctionNumber(), 0
1551 MI->getOperand(2).getImm(), OutContext); 0
1552 const MCExpr *LabelSymExpr= MCSymbolRefExpr::create(LabelSym, OutContext); 0
1553 unsigned PCAdj = (Opc == ARM::MOVi16_ga_pcrel) ? 8 : 4; 0
1554 const MCExpr *PCRelExpr = ----
1555 ARMMCExpr::createLower16(MCBinaryExpr::createSub(GVSymExpr, 0
1556 MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(LabelSymExpr, 0
1557 MCConstantExpr::create(PCAdj, OutContext), 0
1558 OutContext), OutContext), OutContext); 0
1559 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(PCRelExpr)); 0
1560 ----
1561 // Add predicate operands. ----
1562 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1563 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(0)); 0
1564 // Add 's' bit operand (always reg0 for this) ----
1565 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(0)); 0
1566 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInst); 0
1567 return; 0
1568 } 0
1569 case ARM::MOVTi16_ga_pcrel: 0
1570 case ARM::t2MOVTi16_ga_pcrel: { ----
1571 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1572 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opc == ARM::MOVTi16_ga_pcrel 0
1573 ? ARM::MOVTi16 : ARM::t2MOVTi16); ----
1574 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg())); 0
1575 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(MI->getOperand(1).getReg())); 0
1576 ----
1577 unsigned TF = MI->getOperand(2).getTargetFlags(); 0
1578 const GlobalValue *GV = MI->getOperand(2).getGlobal(); 0
1579 MCSymbol *GVSym = GetARMGVSymbol(GV, TF); 0
1580 const MCExpr *GVSymExpr = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(GVSym, OutContext); 0
1581 ----
1582 MCSymbol *LabelSym = ----
1583 getPICLabel(DL.getPrivateGlobalPrefix(), getFunctionNumber(), 0
1584 MI->getOperand(3).getImm(), OutContext); 0
1585 const MCExpr *LabelSymExpr= MCSymbolRefExpr::create(LabelSym, OutContext); 0
1586 unsigned PCAdj = (Opc == ARM::MOVTi16_ga_pcrel) ? 8 : 4; 0
1587 const MCExpr *PCRelExpr = ----
1588 ARMMCExpr::createUpper16(MCBinaryExpr::createSub(GVSymExpr, 0
1589 MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(LabelSymExpr, 0
1590 MCConstantExpr::create(PCAdj, OutContext), 0
1591 OutContext), OutContext), OutContext); 0
1592 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(PCRelExpr)); 0
1593 // Add predicate operands. ----
1594 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1595 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(0)); 0
1596 // Add 's' bit operand (always reg0 for this) ----
1597 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(0)); 0
1598 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInst); 0
1599 return; 0
1600 } 0
1601 case ARM::t2BFi: 0
1602 case ARM::t2BFic: ----
1603 case ARM::t2BFLi: ----
1604 case ARM::t2BFr: ----
1605 case ARM::t2BFLr: { ----
1606 // This is a Branch Future instruction. ----
1607 ----
1608 const MCExpr *BranchLabel = MCSymbolRefExpr::create( 0
1609 getBFLabel(DL.getPrivateGlobalPrefix(), getFunctionNumber(), 0
1610 MI->getOperand(0).getIndex(), OutContext), 0
1611 OutContext); ----
1612 ----
1613 auto MCInst = MCInstBuilder(Opc).addExpr(BranchLabel); 0
1614 if (MI->getOperand(1).isReg()) { 0
1615 // For BFr/BFLr ----
1616 MCInst.addReg(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()); 0
1617 } else { ----
1618 // For BFi/BFLi/BFic ----
1619 const MCExpr *BranchTarget; ----
1620 if (MI->getOperand(1).isMBB()) 0
1621 BranchTarget = MCSymbolRefExpr::create( 0
1622 MI->getOperand(1).getMBB()->getSymbol(), OutContext); 0
1623 else if (MI->getOperand(1).isGlobal()) { 0
1624 const GlobalValue *GV = MI->getOperand(1).getGlobal(); 0
1625 BranchTarget = MCSymbolRefExpr::create( 0
1626 GetARMGVSymbol(GV, MI->getOperand(1).getTargetFlags()), OutContext); 0
1627 } else if (MI->getOperand(1).isSymbol()) { 0
1628 BranchTarget = MCSymbolRefExpr::create( 0
1629 GetExternalSymbolSymbol(MI->getOperand(1).getSymbolName()), 0
1630 OutContext); ----
1631 } else ----
1632 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled operand kind in Branch Future instruction"); 0
1633 ----
1634 MCInst.addExpr(BranchTarget); 0
1635 } ----
1636 ----
1637 if (Opc == ARM::t2BFic) { 0
1638 const MCExpr *ElseLabel = MCSymbolRefExpr::create( 0
1639 getBFLabel(DL.getPrivateGlobalPrefix(), getFunctionNumber(), 0
1640 MI->getOperand(2).getIndex(), OutContext), 0
1641 OutContext); ----
1642 MCInst.addExpr(ElseLabel); 0
1643 MCInst.addImm(MI->getOperand(3).getImm()); 0
1644 } else { ----
1645 MCInst.addImm(MI->getOperand(2).getImm()) 0
1646 .addReg(MI->getOperand(3).getReg()); 0
1647 } ----
1648 ----
1649 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInst); 0
1650 return; 0
1651 } 0
1652 case ARM::t2BF_LabelPseudo: { 0
1653 // This is a pseudo op for a label used by a branch future instruction ----
1654 ----
1655 // Emit the label. ----
1656 OutStreamer->emitLabel(getBFLabel(DL.getPrivateGlobalPrefix(), 0
1657 getFunctionNumber(), ----
1658 MI->getOperand(0).getIndex(), OutContext)); 0
1659 return; 0
1660 } ----
1661 case ARM::tPICADD: { 0
1662 // This is a pseudo op for a label + instruction sequence, which looks like: ----
1663 // LPC0: ----
1664 // add r0, pc ----
1665 // This adds the address of LPC0 to r0. ----
1666 ----
1667 // Emit the label. ----
1668 OutStreamer->emitLabel(getPICLabel(DL.getPrivateGlobalPrefix(), 0
1669 getFunctionNumber(), ----
1670 MI->getOperand(2).getImm(), OutContext)); 0
1671 ----
1672 // Form and emit the add. ----
1673 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(ARM::tADDhirr) 0
1674 .addReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
1675 .addReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
1676 .addReg(ARM::PC) 0
1677 // Add predicate operands. ----
1678 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0
1679 .addReg(0)); 0
1680 return; 0
1681 } ----
1682 case ARM::PICADD: { 0
1683 // This is a pseudo op for a label + instruction sequence, which looks like: ----
1684 // LPC0: ----
1685 // add r0, pc, r0 ----
1686 // This adds the address of LPC0 to r0. ----
1687 ----
1688 // Emit the label. ----
1689 OutStreamer->emitLabel(getPICLabel(DL.getPrivateGlobalPrefix(), 0
1690 getFunctionNumber(), ----
1691 MI->getOperand(2).getImm(), OutContext)); 0
1692 ----
1693 // Form and emit the add. ----
1694 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(ARM::ADDrr) 0
1695 .addReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
1696 .addReg(ARM::PC) 0
1697 .addReg(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()) 0
1698 // Add predicate operands. ----
1699 .addImm(MI->getOperand(3).getImm()) 0
1700 .addReg(MI->getOperand(4).getReg()) 0
1701 // Add 's' bit operand (always reg0 for this) ----
1702 .addReg(0)); 0
1703 return; 0
1704 } ----
1705 case ARM::PICSTR: 0
1706 case ARM::PICSTRB: ----
1707 case ARM::PICSTRH: ----
1708 case ARM::PICLDR: ----
1709 case ARM::PICLDRB: ----
1710 case ARM::PICLDRH: ----
1711 case ARM::PICLDRSB: ----
1712 case ARM::PICLDRSH: { ----
1713 // This is a pseudo op for a label + instruction sequence, which looks like: ----
1714 // LPC0: ----
1715 // OP r0, [pc, r0] ----
1716 // The LCP0 label is referenced by a constant pool entry in order to get ----
1717 // a PC-relative address at the ldr instruction. ----
1718 ----
1719 // Emit the label. ----
1720 OutStreamer->emitLabel(getPICLabel(DL.getPrivateGlobalPrefix(), 0
1721 getFunctionNumber(), ----
1722 MI->getOperand(2).getImm(), OutContext)); 0
1723 ----
1724 // Form and emit the load ----
1725 unsigned Opcode; ----
1726 switch (MI->getOpcode()) { 0
1727 default: 0
1728 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected opcode!"); 0
1729 case ARM::PICSTR: Opcode = ARM::STRrs; break; 0
1730 case ARM::PICSTRB: Opcode = ARM::STRBrs; break; 0
1731 case ARM::PICSTRH: Opcode = ARM::STRH; break; 0
1732 case ARM::PICLDR: Opcode = ARM::LDRrs; break; 0
1733 case ARM::PICLDRB: Opcode = ARM::LDRBrs; break; 0
1734 case ARM::PICLDRH: Opcode = ARM::LDRH; break; 0
1735 case ARM::PICLDRSB: Opcode = ARM::LDRSB; break; 0
1736 case ARM::PICLDRSH: Opcode = ARM::LDRSH; break; 0
1737 } ----
1738 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(Opcode) 0
1739 .addReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
1740 .addReg(ARM::PC) 0
1741 .addReg(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()) 0
1742 .addImm(0) 0
1743 // Add predicate operands. ----
1744 .addImm(MI->getOperand(3).getImm()) 0
1745 .addReg(MI->getOperand(4).getReg())); 0
1746 ----
1747 return; 0
1748 } ----
1749 case ARM::CONSTPOOL_ENTRY: { 0
1750 if (Subtarget->genExecuteOnly()) 0
1751 llvm_unreachable("execute-only should not generate constant pools"); 0
1752 ----
1753 /// CONSTPOOL_ENTRY - This instruction represents a floating constant pool ----
1754 /// in the function. The first operand is the ID# for this instruction, the ----
1755 /// second is the index into the MachineConstantPool that this is, the third ----
1756 /// is the size in bytes of this constant pool entry. ----
1757 /// The required alignment is specified on the basic block holding this MI. ----
1758 unsigned LabelId = (unsigned)MI->getOperand(0).getImm(); 0
1759 unsigned CPIdx = (unsigned)MI->getOperand(1).getIndex(); 0
1760 ----
1761 // If this is the first entry of the pool, mark it. ----
1762 if (!InConstantPool) { 0
1763 OutStreamer->emitDataRegion(MCDR_DataRegion); 0
1764 InConstantPool = true; 0
1765 } ----
1766 ----
1767 OutStreamer->emitLabel(GetCPISymbol(LabelId)); 0
1768 ----
1769 const MachineConstantPoolEntry &MCPE = MCP->getConstants()[CPIdx]; 0
1770 if (MCPE.isMachineConstantPoolEntry()) 0
1771 emitMachineConstantPoolValue(MCPE.Val.MachineCPVal); 0
1772 else ----
1773 emitGlobalConstant(DL, MCPE.Val.ConstVal); 0
1774 return; 0
1775 } ----
1776 case ARM::JUMPTABLE_ADDRS: 0
1777 emitJumpTableAddrs(MI); 0
1778 return; 0
1779 case ARM::JUMPTABLE_INSTS: 0
1780 emitJumpTableInsts(MI); 0
1781 return; 0
1782 case ARM::JUMPTABLE_TBB: 0
1783 case ARM::JUMPTABLE_TBH: ----
1784 emitJumpTableTBInst(MI, MI->getOpcode() == ARM::JUMPTABLE_TBB ? 1 : 2); 0
1785 return; 0
1786 case ARM::t2BR_JT: { 0
1787 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(ARM::tMOVr) 0
1788 .addReg(ARM::PC) 0
1789 .addReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
1790 // Add predicate operands. ----
1791 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0
1792 .addReg(0)); 0
1793 return; 0
1794 } ----
1795 case ARM::t2TBB_JT: 0
1796 case ARM::t2TBH_JT: { ----
1797 unsigned Opc = MI->getOpcode() == ARM::t2TBB_JT ? ARM::t2TBB : ARM::t2TBH; 0
1798 // Lower and emit the PC label, then the instruction itself. ----
1799 OutStreamer->emitLabel(GetCPISymbol(MI->getOperand(3).getImm())); 0
1800 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(Opc) 0
1801 .addReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg()) 0
1802 .addReg(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()) 0
1803 // Add predicate operands. ----
1804 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0
1805 .addReg(0)); 0
1806 return; 0
1807 } ----
1808 case ARM::tTBB_JT: 0
1809 case ARM::tTBH_JT: { ----
1810 ----
1811 bool Is8Bit = MI->getOpcode() == ARM::tTBB_JT; 0
1812 Register Base = MI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1813 Register Idx = MI->getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1814 assert(MI->getOperand(1).isKill() && "We need the index register as scratch!"); 0
1815 ----
1816 // Multiply up idx if necessary. ----
1817 if (!Is8Bit) 0
1818 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(ARM::tLSLri) 0
1819 .addReg(Idx) 0
1820 .addReg(ARM::CPSR) 0
1821 .addReg(Idx) 0
1822 .addImm(1) 0
1823 // Add predicate operands. ----
1824 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0
1825 .addReg(0)); 0
1826 ----
1827 if (Base == ARM::PC) { 0
1828 // TBB [base, idx] = ----
1829 // ADDS idx, idx, base ----
1830 // LDRB idx, [idx, #4] ; or LDRH if TBH ----
1831 // LSLS idx, #1 ----
1832 // ADDS pc, pc, idx ----
1833 ----
1834 // When using PC as the base, it's important that there is no padding ----
1835 // between the last ADDS and the start of the jump table. The jump table ----
1836 // is 4-byte aligned, so we ensure we're 4 byte aligned here too. ----
1837 // ----
1838 // FIXME: Ideally we could vary the LDRB index based on the padding ----
1839 // between the sequence and jump table, however that relies on MCExprs ----
1840 // for load indexes which are currently not supported. ----
1841 OutStreamer->emitCodeAlignment(Align(4), &getSubtargetInfo()); 0
1842 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(ARM::tADDhirr) 0
1843 .addReg(Idx) 0
1844 .addReg(Idx) 0
1845 .addReg(Base) 0
1846 // Add predicate operands. ----
1847 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0
1848 .addReg(0)); 0
1849 ----
1850 unsigned Opc = Is8Bit ? ARM::tLDRBi : ARM::tLDRHi; 0
1851 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(Opc) 0
1852 .addReg(Idx) 0
1853 .addReg(Idx) 0
1854 .addImm(Is8Bit ? 4 : 2) 0
1855 // Add predicate operands. ----
1856 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0
1857 .addReg(0)); 0
1858 } else { ----
1859 // TBB [base, idx] = ----
1860 // LDRB idx, [base, idx] ; or LDRH if TBH ----
1861 // LSLS idx, #1 ----
1862 // ADDS pc, pc, idx ----
1863 ----
1864 unsigned Opc = Is8Bit ? ARM::tLDRBr : ARM::tLDRHr; 0
1865 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(Opc) 0
1866 .addReg(Idx) 0
1867 .addReg(Base) 0
1868 .addReg(Idx) 0
1869 // Add predicate operands. ----
1870 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0
1871 .addReg(0)); 0
1872 } ----
1873 ----
1874 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(ARM::tLSLri) 0
1875 .addReg(Idx) 0
1876 .addReg(ARM::CPSR) 0
1877 .addReg(Idx) 0
1878 .addImm(1) 0
1879 // Add predicate operands. ----
1880 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0
1881 .addReg(0)); 0
1882 ----
1883 OutStreamer->emitLabel(GetCPISymbol(MI->getOperand(3).getImm())); 0
1884 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(ARM::tADDhirr) 0
1885 .addReg(ARM::PC) 0
1886 .addReg(ARM::PC) 0
1887 .addReg(Idx) 0
1888 // Add predicate operands. ----
1889 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0
1890 .addReg(0)); 0
1891 return; 0
1892 } ----
1893 case ARM::tBR_JTr: 0
1894 case ARM::BR_JTr: { ----
1895 // mov pc, target ----
1896 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1897 unsigned Opc = MI->getOpcode() == ARM::BR_JTr ? 0
1898 ARM::MOVr : ARM::tMOVr; 0
1899 TmpInst.setOpcode(Opc); 0
1900 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(ARM::PC)); 0
1901 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg())); 0
1902 // Add predicate operands. ----
1903 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1904 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(0)); 0
1905 // Add 's' bit operand (always reg0 for this) ----
1906 if (Opc == ARM::MOVr) 0
1907 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(0)); 0
1908 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInst); 0
1909 return; 0
1910 } 0
1911 case ARM::BR_JTm_i12: { 0

1913 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1914 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::LDRi12); 0
1915 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(ARM::PC)); 0
1916 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg())); 0
1917 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(MI->getOperand(2).getImm())); 0
1918 // Add predicate operands. ----
1919 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1920 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(0)); 0
1921 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, TmpInst); 0
1922 return; 0
1923 } 0
1924 case ARM::BR_JTm_rs: { 0
1925 // ldr pc, target ----
1926 MCInst TmpInst; 0
1927 TmpInst.setOpcode(ARM::LDRrs); 0
1928 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(ARM::PC)); 0
1929 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(MI->getOperand(0).getReg())); 0
1930 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(MI->getOperand(1).getReg())); 0
1931 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(MI->getOperand(2).getImm())); 0
1932 // Add predicate operands. ----
1933 TmpInst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(ARMCC::AL)); 0

1936 return; 0
1937 } 0
1938 case ARM::BR_JTadd: { 0
1939 // add pc, target, idx ----

1943 .addReg(MI->getOperand(1).getReg()) 0

1945 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0

1954 case ARM::TRAP: { 0

1982 case ARM::t2Int_eh_sjlj_setjmp: 0
1983 case ARM::t2Int_eh_sjlj_setjmp_nofp: ----
1984 case ARM::tInt_eh_sjlj_setjmp: { ----
1985 // Two incoming args: GPR:$src, GPR:$val ----
1986 // mov $val, pc ----
1987 // adds $val, #7 ----
1988 // str $val, [$src, #4] ----
1989 // movs r0, #0 ----
1990 // b LSJLJEH ----
1991 // movs r0, #1 ----
1992 // LSJLJEH: ----
1993 Register SrcReg = MI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1994 Register ValReg = MI->getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
1995 MCSymbol *Label = OutContext.createTempSymbol("SJLJEH"); 0
1996 OutStreamer->AddComment("eh_setjmp begin"); 0

1998 .addReg(ValReg) 0
1999 .addReg(ARM::PC) 0
2000 // Predicate. ----
2001 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0
2002 .addReg(0)); 0
2003 ----
2004 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(ARM::tADDi3) 0
2005 .addReg(ValReg) 0
2006 // 's' bit operand ----
2007 .addReg(ARM::CPSR) 0
2008 .addReg(ValReg) 0
2009 .addImm(7) 0
2010 // Predicate. ----
2011 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0
2012 .addReg(0)); 0
2013 ----
2014 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(ARM::tSTRi) 0
2015 .addReg(ValReg) 0
2016 .addReg(SrcReg) 0
2017 // The offset immediate is #4. The operand value is scaled by 4 for the ----
2018 // tSTR instruction. ----
2019 .addImm(1) 0
2020 // Predicate. ----
2021 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0
2022 .addReg(0)); 0
2023 ----
2024 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(ARM::tMOVi8) 0
2025 .addReg(ARM::R0) 0
2026 .addReg(ARM::CPSR) 0
2027 .addImm(0) 0
2028 // Predicate. ----
2029 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0
2030 .addReg(0)); 0

2032 const MCExpr *SymbolExpr = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Label, OutContext); 0
2033 EmitToStreamer(*OutStreamer, MCInstBuilder(ARM::tB) 0
2034 .addExpr(SymbolExpr) 0
2035 .addImm(ARMCC::AL) 0

2088 .addReg(0)); 0

2111 case ARM::Int_eh_sjlj_longjmp: { 0
